# Copy this to .env on the Droplet and fill in real values.
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-proj-your-key
OPENAI_REALTIME_MODEL=gpt-realtime-2
OPENAI_REALTIME_REASONING_EFFORT=low
OPENAI_REALTIME_VAD_TYPE=semantic_vad
OPENAI_REALTIME_VAD_EAGERNESS=high
MEETING_TRANSCRIPT_LANE_ENABLED=true
OPENAI_TRANSCRIPT_MODEL=gpt-realtime-whisper
MEETING_ROOM_PASSWORD=change-me
MEETING_ROOM_MAX_PARTICIPANTS=10
MEETING_MEMORY_PATH=/app/data/meeting-memory.jsonl
MEETING_BRAIN_INTERVAL=5m
OPENAI_BRAIN_MODEL=gpt-5.5
MEETING_BRAIN_BACKFILL=false
MEETING_TIME_ZONE=America/Los_Angeles
# Session-end rule: a room session ends after the room has been empty this
# long; the prior meeting is silently auto-archived and the next join starts
# a fresh context. Defaults to 30m — only set to override.
# MEETING_IDLE_END_GRACE=30m

# Use the Droplet public IPv4 address here so WebRTC candidates are reachable
# from browsers outside the Docker network.
PION_NAT1TO1_IP=203.0.113.10
PION_UDP_PORT_RANGE=40000-40100

# Optional but recommended for locked-down guest/office networks where direct
# UDP to the Droplet is blocked.
# MEETING_STUN_URLS=stun:stun.l.google.com:19302
# MEETING_TURN_URLS=turn:turn.example.com:3478,turns:turn.example.com:5349
# MEETING_TURN_USERNAME=meetingassist
# MEETING_TURN_CREDENTIAL=replace-with-turn-secret

# Point a real DNS record here, or use a nip.io hostname for a quick demo:
# 203.0.113.10.nip.io
MEETING_HOST=203.0.113.10.nip.io
MEETING_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://203.0.113.10.nip.io

# Optional sidecar Codex runner for Realtime 2 controlled work threads.
# Start with: docker compose --profile codex up -d --build
# Keep Codex auth inside the codex_home Docker volume.
# BONFIRE_AGENT_THREAD_WORKER=codex_exec
# BONFIRE_CODEX_RUNNER_MODE=sidecar_queue
# BONFIRE_CODEX_WORKSPACE_HOST_PATH=/opt/meetingassist-workspace
# BONFIRE_CODEX_CWD=/workspace/meetingassist
# BONFIRE_CODEX_QUEUE_PATH=/app/data/codex-runner-jobs
# BONFIRE_RUNNER_TOKEN=replace-with-openssl-rand-hex-32
# BONFIRE_CODEX_SANDBOX=workspace-write
# BONFIRE_CODEX_APPROVAL_POLICY=never
# BONFIRE_CODEX_REASONING_EFFORT=high
# BONFIRE_CODEX_TIMEOUT=20m

# --- Workflow ticker (card 067) ----------------------------------------------
# ~5-minute status re-scan that relaunches human-APPROVED but stuck proposals
# and any auto_run-lane work carrying a recorded standing approval. Model-free;
# it only ever launches one agent thread per proposal (never /goal or packaging),
# capped per pass. Defaults are safe — leave commented to accept them.
# BONFIRE_WORKFLOW_TICKER_INTERVAL=5m       # duration; 0/off/false/disabled turns it off
# BONFIRE_WORKFLOW_TICKER_DISABLED=false    # truthy disables the ticker
# BONFIRE_WORKFLOW_TICKER_MAX_PER_PASS=2    # max launches per tick

# --- Web Push / installable PWA (card 089) -----------------------------------
# Phone push for durable notifications (chat mentions, task proposals, agent
# milestones). NO env var is strictly required: on first boot the server mints a
# VAPID keypair and persists it to /app/data/vapid-keys.json (kept across
# deploys like users.json). Set the two keys below only to pin a keypair you
# generated yourself (e.g. to keep subscriptions valid across a data wipe).
# WEB_PUSH_VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY=
# WEB_PUSH_VAPID_PRIVATE_KEY=
# Subscriber contact sent in the VAPID JWT (push services require a mailto:).
# WEB_PUSH_SUBSCRIBER=mailto:noreply@thebonfire.xyz
# Device subscriptions persist to /app/data/push-subscriptions.json by default;
# override the path only for test isolation.
# PUSH_SUBSCRIPTIONS_PATH=/app/data/push-subscriptions.json
# NOTE: the container needs outbound HTTPS to the push services
# (fcm.googleapis.com, web.push.apple.com, push.mozilla.org) — ca-certificates
# is already in the runtime image, so no extra setup on a standard Droplet.

# --- Anthropic Fable orchestrator (OPS-3 activation) -------------------------
# The moment ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is set, agent-runner selection defaults to
# anthropic_fable (see selectedAgentRunnerName in agent_runner_iface.go), so
# /goal, grill reports, and packaging deliverables run on Fable instead of the
# Codex fallback. Uncomment the three lines below together: pin the runner
# explicitly (never rely on inference) and pin the sidecar model — an unset
# BONFIRE_CODEX_MODEL means "whatever the Codex CLI defaults to on the host".
# NOTE: the Anthropic org that owns this key must be on 30-day data retention;
# claude-fable-5 returns 400 on every request under zero-data-retention orgs.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-your-key
# BONFIRE_AGENT_RUNNER=anthropic_fable
# BONFIRE_CODEX_MODEL=gpt-5.5

# Orchestrator/deliverable dials, read in agent_runner_anthropic.go. The names
# below must match that file exactly (BONFIRE_ORCHESTRATOR_* for the control
# loop, BONFIRE_DELIVERABLE_* for the contract-bearing /goal deliverable
# subtask) — if a dial is renamed or added there, update this block in the same
# change; the code defaults there are authoritative when a line stays unset.
# Spec target (packaging-os-analysis-2026-07-05): Fable 5 at effort HIGH for
# orchestration + deliverables. Values below mirror that target.
# BONFIRE_ORCHESTRATOR_MODEL=claude-fable-5
# BONFIRE_ORCHESTRATOR_EFFORT=high
# BONFIRE_ORCHESTRATOR_MAX_TURNS=24
# BONFIRE_ORCHESTRATOR_MAX_TOKENS=4096
# BONFIRE_ORCHESTRATOR_TIMEOUT=15m
# BONFIRE_DELIVERABLE_EFFORT=high
# BONFIRE_DELIVERABLE_MAX_TOKENS=32768

# --- Calendar (card 084) -----------------------------------------------------
# The .ics slice needs NO configuration: GET /calendar/event.ics turns a card
# key date into a downloadable all-day event, and the per-milestone "add to
# calendar" button in the key-dates timeline works out of the box. The three
# vars below only RESERVE the future Google Calendar sync seam — set all three
# together and /client-config flips calendar.google to true so the frontend can
# light up a Google button once that wave lands. Half-set = still off.
# GOOGLE_CALENDAR_CLIENT_ID=
# GOOGLE_CALENDAR_CLIENT_SECRET=
# GOOGLE_CALENDAR_REDIRECT_URL=https://$MEETING_HOST/calendar/google/callback
